INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES ('3502', '710', 'tabs_content_body', 'a:1:{i:0;s:5671:\"<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong><em><u>8 NIGHTS 8 DAYS PHILIPPINES </u></em></strong></span></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong><u>Bohol, Cebu, Boracay and Manila</u></strong></span></h3>\r\n<strong><u>Package Details: </u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>DAY 1 ARRIVE BOHOL</strong> On arrival in Bohol, you will be met and transferred by our local representative to your hotel. Overnight in Bohol\r\n\r\n<strong>DAY 2 BOHOL AT LEISURE (B)</strong>Enjoy the day at leisure to discover the island. Overnight in Bohol.\r\n\r\n<strong>DAY 3 DEPART BOHOL  ARRIVE CEBU (B)</strong>\r\n\r\nDepart Bohol and transfer to Cebu via Ferry. On arrival in Cebu, you will be met and transferred by our local representative to your hotel. Overnight in Cebu.\r\n\r\n<strong>DAY 4 CEBU AT LEISURE (B)</strong>\r\n\r\nThe day is at leisure to discover the island with the various activities it offers. Have a massage or go shopping in the city for some local handicrafts or have a seafood meal or just simply relax in your hotel. Overnight in Cebu.\r\n\r\n<strong>DAY 5 CEBU  BORACAY (B)</strong>\r\n\r\nToday, you will fly to Boracay (flight excluded). On arrival, you will be transferred by boat ride to Boracay Island, paradise that boasts powder like sand that is set in the South China Sea. Enjoy the beach. Overnight in Boracay.\r\n\r\n<strong>DAY 6 BORACAY (B)</strong>\r\n\r\nThe day is at leisure to discover the island with the various activities it offers. Have a massage or go parasailing or have a seafood meal or just simply relax in your hotel. Overnight in Boracay.\r\n\r\n<strong>DAY 7 BORACAY - MANILA (B)</strong>\r\n\r\nToday you will fly to Manila (Flight excluded). On arrival in Manila, you will be met and transferred by our local representative to your hotel. The rest of the day is free to explore the city on your own. Overnight in Manila.\r\n\r\n<strong>DAY 8 MANILA (B)</strong>\r\n\r\nDiscover the history of Manila by visiting Casa Manila, San Agustin Church, Fort Santiago, Rizal Park and National Museum and a drive past Roxas Boulevard. Have some free shopping time in Greenhills or SM Mall of Asia. Therese of the day is free. Overnight in Manila.\r\n\r\n<strong>DAY 9 DEPART MANILA (B)</strong>\r\n\r\nToday, you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back home.\r\n\r\n<strong><u>Hotels:</u></strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table style=\"border-color: 000000;\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>5 Star Hotels </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>4 Star Deluxe Hotels </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>4 Star Hotels </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>3 Star Hotels </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>CITY </strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong></strong><strong>AMORITA </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>AMARELA</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MOMO BEACH RESORT</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>LOST HORIZON</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>BOHOL ISLAND</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong></strong><strong>SHANRI-LA MACTAN</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>BLUEWATER MARIBAGO</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>BE RESORT</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>CASTLE PEAK </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>CEBU ISLAND</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong></strong><strong>DISCOVERY SHORES</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>ESTACIO UNO</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>LE SOLEIL BORACAY</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>BORACAY ARWANA</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>BORACAY ISLAND</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MANILA PENINSULA</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MANILA HOTEL</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MANILA PAVILLON</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>RED PLANET HOTEL MAKATI</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MANILA </strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<strong><u>Package Include: </u></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>2 Nights Accommodation in Bohol  Cebu  Boracay  Manila with Breakfast.</li>\r\n 	<li>All overland private transfers with speed boat tickets from Bohol island to Cebu Island.</li>\r\n 	<li>Half day city tour in Manila with English speaking guide and driver.</li>\r\n 	<li>Domestic tickets Manila- Bohol / Cebu  Boracay  Manila Economy Class.</li>\r\n 	<li>Price per person in Double Room in Saudi Riyals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table style=\"border-color: 000000;\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>5 Star Hotels</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>4 Star Deluxe Hotels</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>4 Star Hotels</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>3 Star Hotels</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Hotel / Price</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>SAR 6480</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>SAR 4300</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>SAR 3700</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>SAR 3025</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Price Per Person in Double</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\";}');
