INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES ('5455', '1029', 'tabs_content_body', 'a:2:{i:0;s:10840:\"<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong>VEITNAM HONEY MOON PACKAGE</strong></span></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong>7 NIGHTS 8 DAYS </strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 1, Arrive Hanoi &amp; relaxation</strong><strong>, </strong>upon arrival at Noi Bai airport you will be met by our representative and transferred to hotel for two-night stay. In this afternoon, if you wish to have a quick look at this charming city.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>dinner</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel in Ha Noi for two nights.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 2, Morning visit Hanois city highlights,</strong> enjoy an orientation of Hanoi, its tree-lined streets resplendent with French colonial architecture, including the</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">exquisite, recently restored Opera House. Pass Hoan Kiem Lake, also known as the Lake of the Restored Sword after the legend that surrounds it, en-route to one of the citys many fascinating museums: choose from ancient history, military history or fine arts, depending on your personal interests. Continue to the Temple of Literature, a serene retreat from the busy streets outside. Built in 1070 and dedicated to Confucius, it became Vietnam\'s first university. The best way to experience Hanoi\'s Old Quarter is on foot and next we take a walking tour through an area of the city</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">known as 36 Streets. The oldest continuously developed area of Vietnam, this densely populated section of Hanoi was once an important centre of commerce where goods were sold on the street name of a particular guild. The labyrinthine alleyways are perfect for exploring on foot with names such as Sugar Street, Tin Street and Paper Street. Having lunch at local restaurant (with a Vietnamese set menu) then you will have this afternoon is free at leisure for your own exploration of the city. Alternatively, you may wish to take a chance to visit some nearby villages for a closer look into the rural life.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast, lunch (VN Set menu)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel in Ha Noi</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 3, Hanoi  Ninh Binh,</strong> this morning you are leaving Hanoi and head by road into the</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Vietnamese countryside and beautiful Ninh Binh (95 km, approximately 2 hours).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Upon arrival, begin youre your sightseeing with a visit to Tam Coc, which means three caves which is accessible only by relaxing rowboat. The river trip is wonderful for photographers, especially when local people come to harvest the rice planted along the river, or when they transplant some seedling for the next crops. Due to the huge rock formations jutting out of the rice paddies, the area is often compared with Guilin  China, or more closely, to the limestone islets of Halong Bay in the Tonkin Gulf for their similar geological structures and shapes. Thus, Tam Coc is also called Halong Bay on Land. Check-in to your chosen resort or hotel for lunch and rest of the day is free to relax and enjoy the hotels facilities and the pool. Dinner is on your own expense.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast, lunch</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel/resort in Ninh Binh for one night</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 4, Ninh Binh  Halong Bay,</strong> travel today from Ninh Binh to Halong Bay (170km/approximately 4 hours or so) to board a private junk boat for an overnight cruise.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Halong Bay is one of the most unique landscapes in South East Asia, with more than 3,000 islands rising from the emerald waters of the Gulf of Tonkin. Halong means, Where the dragon descends into the sea and legend has it that the 3,000 islands rising from the clear waters of Halong Bay were created by a great dragon who formed the visible rock outcrops with its flailing tail. Embarking your boat, enjoy a trip through the spectacular rocky scenery, with lunch served on</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">board. The one-night cruise provides views of stunning mountain scenery and floating villages as well as opportunities to explore the natural wonders of the bay such as Surprise Cave and Titop Island.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast, lunch, dinner</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen boat in Ha Long (private cabin in Join-in boat)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 5, Halong Bay  Hanoi  Danang/Hoi An,</strong> after breakfast continue sailing through Halong Bay and enjoy the unique seascape. Brunch is served on-board before mid-morning disembarkation and return by road to Hanoi (165 km/approximately 3 hours). Transfer direct to the Hanoi airport for the late afternoon flight to Danang (1 hour 15 minutes).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On arrival transfer to the chosen resort nearby Hoi An for check-in where you are having 2-night stay. In early evening, you are transferred for the dinner out at one of the best local restaurants with a table reserved at the balcony overlooking to the ancient town.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>brunch, dinner</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel/resort in Hoi An for two nights.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Days 6  Enjoying a cooking class &amp; Hoi An biking,</strong> in this afternoon, guests will make a bike ride to visit the major highlights of the town including Chinese communal houses/pagodas, the unique Japanese covered bridge, architecture reminiscent of traders of a bygone era - Japanese,</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">French, Chinese, and Indian, as well as beautifully preserved ancient houses. You will also have chance to visit the Hoi An local market or shop for art at one of the numerous galleries and enjoy the riverside ambience before returning to your hotel by bike for dinner at your own expenses.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel/resort in Hoi An</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 7, Flying from Da Nang/Hoi An to Ho Chi Minh City (Saigon),</strong> Leaving Hoi An this morning for the transfer back to Da Nang airport for an-hour flight to Saigon (Ho Chi Minh City)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">where you are met, and transferred to the city for check-in. Lunch is on your own. In this afternoon, you will have chance to explore the citys highlights with our local guide, in this essential highlight tour we visit the former Presidential Palace, now preserved as a museum and including the underground communications bunkers, headquarters for the Saigon Government during the American War. Continue to the History Museum, which houses an excellent display tracing the origins of the indigenous, onwards to visit Notre Dame. An impressive neo-Romanesque</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">cathedral in the centre of city. The \'wedding cake\' styled hotel d\'ville and Dong Khoi Street, formerly the centre of haute couture in Saigon when it was known as Rue Catinat. At the end of the tour, guests are transferred to the hotel and free with dinner is on yow own.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel in Saigon for one night</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 8, Free for optional tour available in Ho Chi Minh City,</strong> after breakfast you may wish to have a whole day free at leisure just to relax and enjoy the hotels facilities. Then you may leave your luggage at the hotels concierge for further shopping until time for the transfer back to Saigon airport for onward flight back home</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast</p>\r\n\r\n<table style=\"width: 716px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 198px;\"><strong>5 STAR HOTELS </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 163px;\"><strong>4 STAR HOTELS </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 154px;\"><strong>3 STAR HOTELS </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 152px;\"><strong>CITY </strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 198px;\">Intercontinental Hanoi Hotel</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 163px;\">Silk Path Hotel Han</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 154px;\">La Siesta Hotel Han</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 152px;\"><strong>Hanoi</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 198px;\">Emeralda Resort Ninh Binh</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 163px;\">Ninh Binh Legend Hotel</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 154px;\">Ninh Binh Legend Hotel</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 152px;\"><strong>Ninh Binh</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 198px;\">Paradise Luxury Cruise</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 163px;\">Bhaya Cruise Halong</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 154px;\">Glory Legend Cruise Halong</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 152px;\"><strong>Danang</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 198px;\">Naman Retreat da Nang</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 163px;\">Hoi an Beach Resort Hoi An</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 154px;\">Hoi an Historic Hotel</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 152px;\"><strong>Hoi An</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 198px;\">Pullman Saigon Center Hotel</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 163px;\">Liberty Central Riverside Hotel</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 154px;\">Bay Hotel Saigon</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 152px;\"><strong>Ho Chi Minh</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 198px;\"><strong>SAR 5570 </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 163px;\"><strong>SAR 4300</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 154px;\"><strong>SAR 3790</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 152px;\"><strong>Price Per Person in Double</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\";i:1478934936776;s:8990:\"<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong><u>VEITNAM FAMILY PACKAGE </u></strong></span></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong><u>6 NIGHTS 7 DAYS </u></strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 1: Arrive Ho Chi Minh City (Saigon),</strong> On arrival the family will be met by your tour guide who will transfer you to the chosen hotel by private van. Check in to your hotel and refresh then rest of this first evening will be for your own exploration of the city.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>none</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel in Saigon for two nights</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 2: Free day free in Saigon</strong><strong>,</strong> <strong>Half Day Visit to China Town (4 hours)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Translating to big market, Cholon is located southwest of the citys centre and is the core of its Chinese community. Here you will find Mandarin speakers, ancient pagodas and Chinese script adorning shopfronts. Begin your exploration of the area with a visit to Thien Hau temple. Thien Hau is the Lady of the Sea and it is believed that she can skim across the high seas, locating and rescuing those in trouble. It is not uncommon for the photogenic large coils of incense that hang from the ornate ceiling of this temple to burn for up to three-month at a time. Continue to Cha Tam Church, where President Ngo Dinh Diem sought refuge prior to his assassination in 1963, before heading into the hustle and bustle of BinhTay market, the districts main area for commerce. Finish your tour of Cholon with a visit to a tiny Cao Dai temple hidden away in the centre of the district, where a small group of Caodaist members from this monotheistic religion workshop daily.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel in Saigon</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 3: Ho Chi Minh Citys highlights &amp; fly to Da Nang/Hoi An</strong><strong>, </strong>Buffet breakfast at the hotel and in this morning then guests are transferred directly to SGN airport for mid-day flight to one of the nicest beaches in Central Vietnam  Da Nang beach, on arrival in Danang, you are met by our local guide who will escort you to the chosen hotel where you are staying for two nights. Rest of the afternoon and evening is time for you to relax in resort and enjoy its facilities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen resort in Hoi An for two nights</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 4: Free day for own exploration in Hoi An</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>Half Day Hoi An Countryside Tour (3 hours)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The scenery around Hoi An is quintessential: a Vietnamese landscape waiting to be explored. Narrow canals, peaceful paths and rural roads lead past lush rice paddy fields and overgrown channels to small settlements that have not changed for centuries. The destination for todays excursion is Cam Thanh, a traditional fishing village surrounded by tranquil coconut-palm flanked waterways. Enjoy a comprehensive walk through the village, shaded from the sun by a canopy of bamboo thickets, and learn about the daily life of the fishermen and the local community. Depending on the time of day and the season, there may also be an opportunity to see the local farming community at work.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen resort in Hoi An</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 5: Leaving Hoi An/Da Nang for Hanoi,</strong> in this morning, the family is transferred back to Da Nang airport for a midday flight to Hanoi. On arrival, our representative will transfer you to your hotel in Ha Noi for check-in. You are free for the rest of entire day.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel in Hanoi for two nights</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 6: Full day free in Hanoi</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>Half Day Co Loa Citadel and Bat Trang Pottery Village from Hanoi (4 hours) </strong>A short distance from Hanoi is <strong>Co Loa </strong>which served as Vietnams capital during the 10th century. Its history however, dates back to the 3rd century from which the remains of a massive fortified citadel - the first ever recorded in Vietnamese history - can be seen. Known as old spiral, the city takes its name from the original layout which was based on the shape of a conch shell and had nine walls. Points of interest include a pagoda dedicated to the king\'s daughter Am Mi Chau, and a temple devoted to the king himself.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meals included: </strong>breakfast <strong>Accommodation: </strong>Chosen hotel in Hanoi.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Day 7: Depart Hanoi for flight back home</strong><strong>, </strong>return to Hanoi around noon for check-out then free until time to get the private transfer back to Hanoi airport for</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">your flight home or to next destination</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meal included: </strong>breakfast</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table style=\"width: 698px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 84px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; width: 190px; text-align: center;\"><strong>5 STAR HOTELS </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; width: 145px; text-align: center;\"><strong>4 STAR HOTELS </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; width: 168px; text-align: center;\"><strong>3 STAR HOTELS </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; width: 143px; text-align: center;\"><strong>CITY</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 84px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; width: 190px; text-align: center;\">Pullman Saigon Hotel</td>\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; width: 145px; text-align: center;\">Liberty Central Riverside Hotel</td>\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; width: 168px; text-align: center;\">Bay Hotel SGN</td>\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; width: 143px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Ho Chi Minh</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 84px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; width: 190px; text-align: center;\">Boutique Hoi An Resort</td>\r\n<td style=\"height: 84px; 