INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES ('6176', '1153', 'tabs_content_body', 'a:3:{i:0;s:8050:\"<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong>Helsinki, Stockholm, Copenhagen and Oslo</strong></span></h3>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong>Scandinavia in One Week</strong></span></h3>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong>6700 SR Per Person In Double Room</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Program Details:</u></strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 1: Arrival to Helsinki -Sightseeing Start</u></strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Arrival in <strong>Helsinki</strong><strong>, </strong>the capital of Finland. Transfer from Vantaa airport to your hotel. Spend some time to see the charm of Helsinki and board the site seeing bus. Helsinki is a modern European cultural city whose urban cosmopolitan lifestyle exists in perfect harmony with nature. Surrounded by the sea and its own exotic archipelago, Helsinki offers visitors an endless number of possibilities. Take the Helsinki City Tour with recorded commentary and sound effects, giving you a wide variety of information about Helsinki. The many sights include the <strong>Senate Square</strong>, <strong>Uspenski Cathedral</strong>, the <strong>Parliament Building</strong> and the <strong>Olympic Stadium, </strong>the <strong>Sibelius Monument, </strong>the <strong>Temppeliaukio Church, </strong>etc.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 2: Helsinki Sightseeing  Evening Cruise to Stockholm</u></strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong>After breakfast take the boat to the <strong>Suomenlinna fortress</strong>. Suomenlinna or Viapori (Finnish), or Sveaborg (Swedish), is an inhabited sea fortress built on six islands, today within Helsinki, the capital of Finland. It is a UNESCO World Heritage site and popular with both tourists and locals, who enjoy it as a picturesque picnic site. Originally named Sveaborg (Fortress of Svea), it was renamed Suomenlinna (Castle of Finland) in 1918 for patriotic and nationalist reasons, though it is still also known by its original name.\r\nBy evening 16:00 board the overnight ferry for Stockholm</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 3: Stockholm Sightseeing</u></strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast on board, arrive in <strong>Stockholm</strong> the <strong><em>Capital of Scandinavia</em></strong> at 09:30. You are transferred to your hotel where you can keep the luggage as the rooms may not be ready until 2 PM. You will either get your Sightseeing card (valid throughout your stay) giving you access to major museums and free usage of public transportation. As an option to this card, we may provide you Sit In Coach bus/ boat tour ticket. Start your sightseeing through a comfortable bus with a fabulous view. The trip provides you with exciting information about the sights as you drive or sail past them. See the whole of Stockholm in 90 minutes. The trip shows you the most famous buildings and views, including a stop at <strong>Fjllgatan</strong>, where the view of Stockholm\'s islands and waters is truly wonderful. This trip continues further to one-hour boat ride. Spend the rest of the day on your own to discover the beauty on water.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 4: Transfer to Copenhagen or Oslo</u></strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast spend some time to discover Stockholm\'s famous shopping streets and malls. In the afternoon take the 5 hours train journey to reach the lovely city of <strong>Copenhagen</strong>, the capital of Denmark. Before your train arrives do not miss the famous resund bridge connecting Sweden with Denmark. Copenhagen got its name from the word \"kbenhavn\", which means \"Merchants harbour\". It is a captivating, friendly city where there is always something wonderful around the next corner - to see, smell, taste, feel or listen to.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 5: Copenhagen Sightseeing  Evening Cruise to Oslo or (Copenhagen)</u></strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">You will be provided a voucher for hop on hop off bus tour which is valid for 24 hours. The tour passes by the <strong>Tivoli</strong><strong> Gardens</strong> and the <strong>Ny Carlsberg Glyptotek</strong>. The tour drives through the colourful canal district and past the <strong>National</strong><strong> Museum</strong>, by <strong>Christiansborg</strong><strong> Palace</strong>, home to the Danish Parliament. The trip continues on to the old <strong>Stock Exchange</strong> and across <strong>Kongens Nytorv</strong>, where you can see the <strong>Royal Theatre</strong>, world famous for its Royal Ballet. You will also go past the colourful harbour district of Nyhavn to <strong>Amalienborg Palace</strong> - Winter residence of the Royal Family. Here you have the opportunity to see the changing of the Guard. This may be followed by a visit to the <strong>Gefion Fountain </strong>and <strong>The Little Mermaid</strong>, inspired by H. C. Andersen\'s fairy tale. During the tour, you pay a visit to one of the many magnificent churches in Copenhagen as well as passing by <strong>Rosenborg Castle</strong>, where the Crown Jewels are protected by the Royal Guard. A taxi will transfer you from the hotel to the cruise harbour at 15:30. At 16:00, board the cruise to Oslo for the wonderful cruise on the North Sea and night long party.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 6: Oslo Sightseeing  Evening Cruise to Copenhagen or (Oslo)</u></strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Arrive in <strong>Oslo</strong> after breakfast on board at 09:30. Take the connecting bus from the pier to arrive in the city and start your 2 hours sightseeing tour. The port town of Oslo is the capital of Norway Oslo celebrated its 1000 years anniversary in the year 2000. Until 1814, it was known as <strong>Christiania</strong> after the Danish-Norwegian king. The city is beautifully situated at the head of Oslo Fjord surrounded by forested ridges, and this very location gives Oslo unexpected qualities for a national capital. In Oslo tour, you explore the <strong>Royal</strong><strong> Palace</strong><strong>, </strong>the <strong>City Hall, </strong>the <strong>Akershus </strong>fortress, <strong>Holmenkollen Ski</strong> arena<strong> and Vigeland Sculpture park.</strong>\r\nBy evening 16:00, board the cruise back to Copenhagen to join the party.\r\nAs an option, you may stay one night in Oslo and depart from Oslo on day-7.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 7: Departure from Copenhagen</u></strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast on board arrive in Copenhagen at 09:30. You are then transferred to the airport or the train station for your onward destination.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><u>Program Including:</u></p>\r\n\r\n<ul dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Daily breakfast and hotel accommodation in <u>4 stars category hotels</u></strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Overnight cruises to Helsinki-Stockholm and Copenhagen-Oslo with own inside cabin</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>All city transfers from airport / station / cruise terminal to hotels and back (if the distance is more than 800 meters)</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Train journey in Scandinavia</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Regular Sightseeing as per itinerary above</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em><u>4 Capitals of Scandinavia Package can also be started from Copenhagen / Oslo / Stockholm as:</u></em></strong><strong><em>\r\n</em></strong>\r\n<strong>Oslo-Copenhagen-Stockholm-Helsinki-Stockholm</strong></p>\r\nCopenhagen-Oslo-Stockholm-Helsinki-Stockholm\r\n\r\nStockholm-Helsinki-Stockholm-Oslo-Copenhagen\";i:1482381200357;s:8965:\"<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong>Scandinavia Classic Trip</strong></span></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong>Copenhagen, Oslo, Flm, Bergen, Stockholm and Helsinki in</strong><strong>10 Days </strong></span></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong>10300 SR Per Person In Double Room</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Program Details:</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 1: Arrival Copenhagen  Transfer to Hotel</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Arrival in Copenhagen, the capital of Denmark. Transfer from airport to your hotel. Spend some time to see the charm of Copenhagen on your own.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 2: Copenhagen Sightseeing- Evening Cruise to Oslo</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You will be provided with a voucher for hop on hop off bus tour which is valid for 24 hours. The tour passes by the <strong>Tivoli Gardens</strong> and the <strong>Ny Carlsberg Glyptotek</strong>. The tour drives through the colourful canal district and past the <strong>National Museum</strong>, by <strong>Christiansborg Palace</strong>, home to the Danish Parliament. The trip continues on to the old <strong>Stock Exchange</strong> and across <strong>Kongens Nytorv</strong>, where you can see the <strong>Royal Theatre</strong>, world famous for its Royal Ballet. You will also go past the colourful harbour district of Nyhavn to <strong>Amalienborg Palace</strong> - Winter residence of the Royal Family. Here you have the opportunity to see the changing of the Guard. This may be followed by a visit to the <strong>Gefion Fountain </strong>and <strong>The Little Mermaid</strong>, inspired by H. C. Andersen\'s fairy tale. During the tour, you pay a visit to one of the many magnificent churches in Copenhagen as well as passing by <strong>Rosenborg Castle</strong>, where the Crown Jewels are protected by the Royal Guard. A taxi will transfer you from the hotel to the cruise harbour at 15:30. At 16:00, board the cruise to Oslo for the wonderful cruise on the North Sea and night long party. Your own inside cabins with washroom will be booked with breakfast.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 3: Oslo Sightseeing  Overnight in Oslo</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Arrive in <strong>Oslo</strong> after breakfast on board at 09:30. The port town of Oslo is the capital of Norway Oslo celebrated its 1000 years anniversary in the year 2000. Until 1814, it was known as <strong>Christiania </strong>after the Danish-Norwegian king. The city is beautifully situated at the head of Oslo Fjord surrounded by forested ridges, and this very location gives Oslo unexpected qualities for a national capital. Start the Oslo tour which allows you to see all of Oslos main attractions for instance, the <strong>Royal Palace, </strong>the <strong>City Hall, </strong>the <strong>Akershus </strong>fortress<strong>. </strong>Spend some time on the controversial <strong>Vigeland Sculpture park. </strong>Check in to your hotel after the tour finishes. Spend the evening at Karl Johan street.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 4: Train Transfer to Flam  Overnight in Flam</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast board the train to Flam. The four hours journey is full of natures best offerings so be ready to enjoy and shoot the picturesque memories. After Myrdal, change to the 1 hour journey over the world famous Flmbana that stops on the way to let you enjoy the waterfalls. Lookout for the ferries dancing on the rocks with surreal musicCheck in to your hotel and enjoy the evening at your leisure.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 5: Transfer to Bergan via Bale strand by Fjord Express Boat</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast, spend the day in some easy trekking on the Flm valley. The green pastures and the cascading waterfalls are simply spectacular. In the afternoon 15:00, take the express boat through Sognefjrd, the largest fjord in Norway that takes you through shows the various places e.g. the famous to reach Bergen crossing famous Bale strand on the way. <strong><em>Note: Boat is available in summer time only, so in winter we use train.</em></strong>\r\nArrive Bergen in the evening and spend overnight at your hotel.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 6: Bergen Sightseeing  Overnight in Bergen</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast discover Bergen through the Flibanen funicular that takes you on top of the Fli mountain to give you view of Bergen from different perspectives. After spending time to buy souveniers and enjoying coffee in the cafeteria take the train back. Discover the UNESCO heritage of Bryggen,Fish Market and beautiful parks in the centre of Bergen.\r\nSpend the evening in discovering the local food from a pool of restaurants on the harbour.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 7: Flight to Stockholm  Overnight</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast, we provide the transfer to the airport for the flight to reach Stockholm - <em>The Capital of Scandinavia</em>. On arrival in Stockholm you are transferred to your hotel.\r\nSpend the time at your own leisure to discover Stockholm - the Capital of Scandinavia. Stockholm full of shopping streets and houses exclusive brand names as Lindex, H&amp;M, hlens, Ikea etc.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 8: Stockholm Sightseeing  Evening Cruise to Helsinki</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You will either get your Sightseeing card (valid throughout your stay) giving you access to major museums and free usage of public transportation. As an option to this card, we may provide you Sit in Coach bus/ boat tour ticket. Start your sightseeing through a comfortable bus with a fabulous view. The trip provides you with exciting information about the sights as you drive or sail past them. See the whole of Stockholm in 90 minutes. The trip shows you the most famous buildings and views, including a stop at <strong>Fjllgatan</strong>, where the view of Stockholm\'s islands and waters is truly wonderful. This trip continues further to one-hour boat ride. Spend the rest of the day on your own to discover the beauty on water. Taxi will transfer you from the hotel at 15:40 to the cruise harbor. Check in starts around 16:00 hrs. at the cruise terminal from where the ship for Helsinki departs at 1700 hrs. An own inside cabin with breakfast will be booked.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 9: Arriving to Helsinki  Sightseeing  Departure</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After buffet breakfast on board, arrive in <strong>Helsinki, </strong>the capital of Finland. We suggest you to keep your luggage in the cabin or at the cabin lockers and proceed straight to the waiting coach for Helsinki sightseeing. Helsinki City Tour with recorded commentary and sound effects, giving you a wide variety of information about Helsinki. The many sights include the <strong>Senate Square</strong>, <strong>Uspenski Cathedral</strong>, the <strong>Parliament Building</strong> and the <strong>Olympic Stadium, </strong>the <strong>Sibelius Monument, </strong>the <strong>Temppeliaukio Church, </strong>etc. Spend some time on your own to discover the Market Hall and return back to the cruise terminal for your return back to Stockholm.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 10: Arrival to Stockholm  Departure Back</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast on board, arrive back in Stockholm at 10:00. From the cruise harbour, you are transferred back to Arlanda airport for your flight back.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Package Including:</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>Daily breakfast and hotel accommodation in 3 or 4 stars category hotels</li>\r\n 	<li>Overnight cruises to Copenhagen - Oslo and Stockholm - Helsinki with own inside cabin with beds and wash rooms.</li>\r\n 	<li>All city transfers from airport / station / cruise terminal to hotels and back (if the distance is more than 800 meters)</li>\r\n 	<li>Train journey from Oslo to Flm on the scenic Flmbana</li>\r\n 	<li>Fjord cruise on the largest fjord in Norway Sognefjord by express boat Flm-Bale strand-Bergen (summer time only - 1st May to 30th September)</li>\r\n 	<li>Air flight from Bergen to Stockholm</li>\r\n 	<li>Regular Sightseeing as per itinerary below</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em><u>Classic tour of Scandinavia can also be started from Bergen, Stockholm or Oslo and ended in any other main Capital city</u></em></strong></p>\";i:1482381200752;s:4087:\"<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong>ON Board THE BALTIC In 5 Days Cruise</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Program Details:</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 1: Departure from Stockholm 1900 PM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Check in at the Cruise harbour in Stockholm at least 90 minutes before the cruise departure time.\r\nIn the evening, enjoy the on-board entertainment and buffet dinner on board (included in the luxury package).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 2: Arrival to Tallinn 11.30 AM  Departure 1900 PM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enjoy the sea breakfast on board and arrive in Tallinn, the capital of Estonia.\r\nDeparture at 19:00</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 3: Arrival in Betersburg 9.30 AM  Departure 1900 PM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Arrive in St. Petersburg in the morning and after breakfast take the St. Petersburg City tour in a shuttle bus which is part of the package.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Optional excursions available</u></strong>\r\nBuilt on more than 100 islands and linked by 600 bridges, St. Petersburg offers a stunning array of Russian baroque and neo-classical architecture. Main sights include the Bronze Horseman, St. Isaacs Square, Palace Square, Peter and Paul Fortress, the Battleship of Aurora, Smolny and Nevsky Prospekt, the city\'s main thoroughfare and most famous street. Cruise departs at 19:00.\r\nAfter buffet dinner (included inthe luxury package), on board entertainment awaits you on MS Anastasia.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 4: Arrival to Helsinki 8.00 AM  Departure 1600 PM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enjoy the sea breakfast on board and arrive in Helsinki, the capital of Finland. Spend time to discover Helsinki. Departure for Stockholm at 16:00</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Day 5: Arrival in Stockholm at 8.00 AM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Luxury package includes</u></strong><strong><u> </u></strong><strong><u>( </u></strong><strong><u>5370</u></strong><strong><u> SR Per Person In Double Cabin</u></strong><strong><u>)</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>Accommodation in Commodore cabin</li>\r\n 	<li>Deluxe breakfast with Champagne and caviar</li>\r\n 	<li>4 Buffet dinners (includes coffee, tea, water.</li>\r\n 	<li>Onboard entertainment, Port dues, Taxes and duties</li>\r\n 	<li>City shuttle bus in St Petersburg (not any regulartour</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Standard package includes </u></strong><strong><u>(</u></strong><strong><u>2900</u></strong><strong><u> SR Per Person In Double Cabin)</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>Accommodation in inside cabin</li>\r\n 	<li>Onboard entertainment</li>\r\n 	<li>City shuttle bus in St Petersburg (not any regulartour)</li>\r\n 	<li>Port dues, Taxes and duties.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Requirements for visitors without Visa:</u></strong></p>\r\n- Return must be in 72 hours, starting from the arrival to St. Petersburg\r\n- Passport with more than 6 months validity\r\n- Shuttle bus ticket (included in the package cost)\r\n- Hotel/hostel reservation (in case of passenger stays overnight in St. Petersburg)\r\n\r\nFor visa-free entrance you need to provide following passport details when you book your cruise:\r\n First name(s) and surname\r\n Date and place of birth\r\n Passport number and expiry date\r\n Citizenship\r\n\r\nConsider the visa regulations updates (if any) stated regulations are valid at the time of publication only. Scandinavian Packages cannot accept any responsibility for the changes Russian authorities might apply to the visa regulations.\r\n\r\nIf you prefer to explore St. Petersburg on your own, you should obtain an individual visa. The visa must be obtained in your home country before the beginning of the cruise.\";}');
